<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,302,328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet “lusca” (single-eyed, monocular) refers to the presence of a rounded pit with a raised thickened central area, resembling an eye.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,374,400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Distribution:</emphasis>
—To date, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusev &amp; Kezlya" authorityYear="2021" box="[469,675,374,400]" class="Chrysophyceae" family="Mallomonadaceae" genus="Mallomonas" kingdom="Chromista" order="Synurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="lusca">
<emphasis box="[469,675,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Mallomonas lusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been observed in six localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1097,1196,374,400]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. In addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[1403,1451,375,401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">type</typeStatus>
locality, it has been found in two other waterbodies in 
<collectingRegion box="[732,969,410,436]" country="Vietnam" name="Binh Thuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Binh Thuan Province</collectingRegion>
and in 
<collectingRegion box="[1048,1175,410,437]" country="Vietnam" name="Khanh Hoa" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Khanh Hoa</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1227,1335,410,437]" country="Vietnam" name="Dong Nai" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Dong Nai</collectingRegion>
Provinces (
<tableCitation box="[143,227,446,472]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,304,328]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Ecological conditions and distributional records for Mallomonas lusca sp. nov. (Cond.—specific conductance, T—temperature, Chla—chlorophyll a)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/52A0661EFFADFFA209BA0E17FDBCFED6" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" tableUuid="52A0661EFFADFFA209BA0E17FDBCFED6">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Scales of this species were also reported from one locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[938,1041,446,472]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Durrschmidt, M. &amp; Croome, R." box="[1055,1392,446,473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" pagination="285 - 298" refId="ref3718" refString="Durrschmidt, M. &amp; Croome, R. (1985) Mallomonadaceae (Chrysophyceae) from Malaysia and Australia. Nordic Journal of Botany 5: 285 - 298. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1756 - 1051.1985. tb 01657. x" type="journal article" year="1985">Dürrschmidt &amp; Croome 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,357,482,508]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Observations:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusev &amp; Kezlya" authorityYear="2021" box="[385,591,482,508]" class="Chrysophyceae" family="Mallomonadaceae" genus="Mallomonas" kingdom="Chromista" order="Synurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="lusca">
<emphasis box="[385,591,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Mallomonas lusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in meso- and eutrophic water bodies within a pH range of 6.0–6.7, specific conductance of 23 to 311 μS 
<superScript attach="left" box="[557,604,518,545]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">cm-1</superScript>
, and temperature 29–34 ºC (
<tableCitation box="[925,1009,518,544]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,304,328]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Ecological conditions and distributional records for Mallomonas lusca sp. nov. (Cond.—specific conductance, T—temperature, Chla—chlorophyll a)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/52A0661EFFADFFA209BA0E17FDBCFED6" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" tableUuid="52A0661EFFADFFA209BA0E17FDBCFED6">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
